description.narrative:
- Institutional arrangements in place for climate change adaptation planning, implementation and coordination are in place;
- Monitoring, reporting and verification mechanisms for climate change adaption planning and implementation are in place;
- Existence of operational standards/procedures/planning tools developed to advance climate change data collection and management; and Number of people capacitated on climate change adaptation planning and management
- Number of sectoral plans that incorporate CCA, developed/or updated and approved;
- Procedures in place among sector agencies to conduct iterative vulnerability assessments; and Number of people trained to conduct VAs, generate and prioritize adaptation actions;
- Tertiary education program on climate change is in place.
- National climate change adaptation finance coordination mechanism is in place;
- Number of subnational/ district officials trained on CCA mainstreaming, planning and implementation;
- Number of private sector stakeholders that benefited from awareness raising on physical CC processes, risks and opportunities.

comment.narrative:
- No horizontal or vertical institutional structure or procedures exist for climate change adaptation planning and implementation;
- No monitoring, reporting and verification system for climate change adaption planning and implementation exists;
- Climate Change Center has limited capacity and underdeveloped procedures to serve as knowledge management institution for climate change adaptation and planning in Tajikistan.
- Climate change adaptation considerations currently NOT integrated or mainstreamed into priority sector governance, planning, and budgeting activities;
- Priority sector agencies lack procedures and capacities for conducting vulnerability assessments or for prioritizing adaptation measures;
- No tertiary education program focusing on climate change exists in Tajikistan; no permanent capacity building and/or professional development opportunities exist for climate change.
- No finance coordination mechanisms exist; priority sectors lack the ability to estimate costs of climate impacts as well as costs of adaptation measures;
- Provincial, district and subdistrict administration officials, CEP staff, COLUGC staff, and Ministry of Agriculture staff have low understanding of climate change processes and guidance and no scale-appropriate guidance on mainstreaming;
- Private sector unaware of climate change physical processes, impacts, and the need for adaptation or appropriate adaptation actions.

- Institutional structure and arrangements for climate change adaptation policy and implementation clarified and formalized;
- Horizontal/vertical coordination framework established;
- Monitoring and evaluation system for implementing strategic priorities established;
- Stakeholder participation and inclusiveness guidelines established and implemented;
- Indicators, methodology, and reporting system for climate change adaptation developed;
- Inter-ministerial coordination for monitoring and reporting facilitated;
- Periodic updating of climate change process and adaptation indicators implemented;
- Standards and procedures for climate change data and information developed;
- Capacity development program at Climate Change Center established;
- Planning tools for climate change adaptation developed.
- Sectoral focal points appointed and working groups formed;
- Sectoral institutional and legal reviews conducted;
- Strategy for updating regulatory framework (secondary legislation) formulated;
- Strategic planning procedures to incorporate climate change adaptation revised;
- Baseline analysis in priority sectors conducted;
- Priority sector vulnerability assessments conducted;
- Adaptation options for priority sectors generated and prioritized;
- Capacity building infrastructure established;
- Capacity development curricula formulated.
- Knowledge products, awareness-raising materials, and relevant tools for subnational authorities and other stakeholders developed;
- Private sector baseline analysis and strategy formulated.
